{
  "stem": "15686.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we waited there about three weeks, because apparently, it was very difficult to get space on board a ship.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Only the neutral ships could cross the Atlantic with civilians on board.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And there weren't many neutral countries.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There was Switzerland, but they had no Navy.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] They had no ships.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And that left Portugal or Sweden.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we were-- we were too far away from Sweden.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So the Portuguese ships were all booked in advance for months and months and months.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So we didn't know which ship we would get on and when.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But after about, oh, I think it was about, again, three weeks or so, we were told that we would leave the next day.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And it was a Portuguese ship called the And the was like a big shuttle between Lisbon and New York.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "There are literally thousands of refugees in the United States that came here on that ship.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And it was, at that time, one of the largest passenger ships afloat.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "By today's standards, it's very small.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But now, we had-- the ship had-- was supposed to go in eight days from Lisbon to New York.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "That was the standard time in those days.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And they had enough provisions for eight or nine days on board for all the people who-- the refugee kids went in steerage, which was way down below the water level.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And that were-- we slept in bunks four high.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "On sort of a straw mattress, but we didn't care.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We were just glad to get out of there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And since food and things like that were hard to buy in Europe-- every country had shortages, even the neutral ones-- the ships were usually replenished in the United States.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "So they had enough food on board for eight days.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
